steps
Once we have spring security in our dependency, it automatically gives us a login form.
username = user
password = The generated password when we start the application on the console.
Once you login, it saves us the logic of maintaining the session.
Once you go to localhost:8080/logout, it also logs the user out.
we can set the username and password in the application.properties.

normally
when a client sends a request, the controller receives the request and sends a response.
But with spring security, the client sends a request and spring security intercepts it.
spring security invokes the servlets (filters that run behind the scenes) and they are a chain of filters.
so from the filter chain to the front controller(dispatcher servlet) and then to our created controller.
The response too goes from our controller, through the filter chain and back to the client.

